The Federal Government has warned that it will not tolerate the recruitment of Nigerians as foreign fighters in Ukraine. The government in a state­ment signed by the spokes­person of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Francisca Omayuli, said it is already in talks with the Ukrainian authorities to forestall such action. The remarks followed reports that Nigerian vol­unteers are being drafted into the Ukrainian army at the Ukrainian Embassy in Abuja. You’re Example Of God-Fearing, Loyal, Patriotic Public… World Cup Playoff: Siasia Faults Eguavoen On Invitation Of Some… According to the Federal Government, “The Ministry of Foreign Affairs had con­tacted the embassy to verify the speculation.” The statement added that “the Ukrainian Embassy refuted the allegation,” but confirmed that a number of Nigerians had approached the embassy indicating their will­ingness to fight on the side of Ukraine in its ongoing conflict with Russia. “Furthermore, the em­bassy clarified that the Ukrainian government is not admitting foreign volunteer fighters and as such dissoci­ated itself from the claim that it is requesting $1,000 from each Nigerian volunteer for air ticket and visa. “As a responsible member of the international commu­nity and consistent with our obligations under internation­al law, Nigeria discourages the use of mercenaries anywhere in the world and will not tol­erate the recruitment, in Ni­geria, of Nigerians as merce­naries to fight in Ukraine or anywhere in the world. “The Federal Government will continue to engage with the embassy of Ukraine in Nigeria and other relevant authorities to prevent this possibility.”